columns.label: General Practice Code
columns.description: General Practice Code

columns.label: General Practice Name
columns.description: General Practice Name
columns.comments: This is the most recent name for the practice operating under this code, which may be different to the name it had at the time the data was extracted.

columns.label: Primary Care Network Code
columns.description: Primary Care Network Code
columns.comments: Not applicable up to December 2018. This shows as "Unaligned" for those practices not currently members of a Primary Care Network. Shows as "NA" for reporting periods prior to the introduction of PCNs. This information is provided for reference only and should not be used to attempt to quantify the PCN workforce, as these figures relate only to the general practice workforce. Information is taken from reference data that reflects the list of active PCNs and their constituent practices at the start of the month and so subsequent changes to PCN membership or their names by the time the date the data was extracted may not be reflected in this file.

columns.label: Whether GP records for this practice were "Fully provided", provided but requiring some record-level estimations of missing hours ("Includes FTE Estimates"), or estimated for at a Sub-ICB Location level ("Fully Estimated") where no valid data was recorded under this staff group at the practice. From June 2018 onwards, for those practices which had Sub-ICB Location-level estimation applied, this field also states where records were submitted but failed validation or were for staff who had left or not yet joined ("No valid or current data") or had not submitted any data ("No data provided").

columns.label: Total GPs Headcount
columns.description: Total GPs Headcount
columns.comments: From February 2023, 'NA' refers to 'not available' and denotes practices who provided 0 records or 0 valid records overall for this staff group in the current extraction (excluding TIS data). These practices submitted no records to NWRS for this staff group, submitted records which failed data quality validation rules, or their submitted records are staff who have left or not yet joined. These practices will form part of the Sub-ICB Location level estimates for their area. The GP_SOURCE field indicates the type of no data the practice falls under for this staff group.

PRAC_NAME.label: General Practice Name
PRAC_NAME.comments: This is the most recent name for the practice operating under this code, which may be different to the name it had at the time the data was extracted.

PCN_CODE.label: Primary Care Network Code
PCN_CODE.comments: Not applicable up to December 2018. This shows as "Unaligned" for those practices not currently members of a Primary Care Network. Shows as "NA" for reporting periods prior to the introduction of PCNs. This information is provided for reference only and should not be used to attempt to quantify the PCN workforce, as these figures relate only to the general practice workforce. Information is taken from reference data that reflects the list of active PCNs and their constituent practices at the start of the month and so subsequent changes to PCN membership or their names by the time the date the data was extracted may not be reflected in this file.

GP_SOURCE.label: Whether GP records for this practice were "Fully provided", provided but requiring some record-level estimations of missing hours ("Includes FTE Estimates"), or estimated for at a Sub-ICB Location level ("Fully Estimated") where no valid data was recorded under this staff group at the practice. From June 2018 onwards, for those practices which had Sub-ICB Location-level estimation applied, this field also states where records were submitted but failed validation or were for staff who had left or not yet joined ("No valid or current data") or had not submitted any data ("No data provided").
